						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							A roadrunner&#8217;s greatest threats are hawks, skunks, coyotes, and raccoons. Although the last three creatures listed prey mainly on eggs in the nest. Roadrunners rely largely on their fast legs to outrun predators. They also hide in bushes and make their nests above ground in order to escape predators
