				</navigationLabel>
				<contentItems>
					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							Roadrunners are fast runners who can reach speeds of up to 20 miles (32 km/h) per hour. They use their tails as a rudder to steer while running at top speed. They are also able to jump straight up in the air when small birds or flying insects are overhead.  These birds are also known to work with another roadrunner when hunting bigger prey, like snakes.
						</text>
